PerpetualMorningCowboi…

He goes around howdying unsuspecting strangers all day. Insisting it’s the morning. He does this everyday.

Nobody asks him to do this. Nobody needs him to do this. He does it anyway.

If anyone insists it is not morning he has a violently upset reaction. It does not register to him. It must always be morning. Does he actually believe this?

Why does PerpetualMorningCowboi do this?

It seems so nonsensical.

Perhaps PerpetualMorningCowboi can’t let himself know that time has passed him by. 

Perhaps he feels he cannot admit to  himself that he wasted his time. 

Does PerpetualMorningCowboi live in denial. Needing to insist on this lie so much, hoping it could in some way bend reality, so that he did not waste the mornings of his life.

Maybe if he convinces everyone that the morning has not passed. Then perhaps he could somehow reclaim the time he once had and wishes he took advantage of.

He does this everyday. All day.

Until the sun starts to set.

He soon realizes that in all his time regretting his wasted mornings. He ended up living his afternoons in denial and deep regret and fear. Pushing this regret and fear onto others.

He has now wasted his afternoons. He’s alone.

Living his dusks. Also in deep inescapable regret.

With no precious memories to look back on to make the impending setting of the sun less bleak.

He’s unable to see the beauty in the setting sun. Because it doesn’t show him a life well lived. Where some might see a tapestry of radiant colors representing a life full of cherished memories and colors. Where some might be able to find solace in those memories, making the approaching darkness less daunting. He sees the sun creeping towards the horizon only akin to the sand running out of an hourglass.

PerpetualMorningCowboi stares at the horizon. Trying to hold onto the time he has left. Finally wanting to live in this moment. But this isn’t cherishing time. He’s not embracing this time. He’s clutching onto it desperately. He doesn’t know anything else.

He sheds a single tear. Wishing he just let go of his contempt for how he spent his morning. Wishing he had the foresight to just live his afternoon how he wanted. Despite the morning. Instead of lying to himself. Instead of blaming others and being cold.

He was looking backwards all this time. Only focusing on what time he had wasted. Instead of looking forward and seeing all that he had left. As time passed, only looking backward, the time he wasted only increased. Once he finally turned around, all he saw was what little time he had left.

The sun sets.

PerpetualMorningCowboi lets out a sigh…

If someone extended a “howdy” to this old cowboi. He would plead to you; “don’t be like me” “don’t be a perpetualmorningcowboi”

Just be… “cowboi”





Or maybe he was just batshit crazy and we should just ignore him and cross to the other side of the street if we see him pass. Who knows. Who cares.

I hope you like my short story.

It’s new to feel someone wants to know those parts and understands and wants to understand all parts. Terrifying only because I’m not used to it.

I grew up feeling like I had to be enough to be cared about at all. Like love was something that could be taken away at any moment if I messed up or upset someone. Because that’s what it was like with my mother at the time. There was no consistency and I never knew if she was going to yell about something because she’s stressed or overcompensate with guilt and act like she cares for a brief moment.

The unknown and feeling undeserving does not come from anything you’ve done at all. In fact, you’re proving those unhealthy instincts wrong. The idea that’s drilled into my head about being unworthy of being cared about and understood and accepted in such a wonderful wholistic way. You seem to care in a non transactional, non bitter, and honest way.

I’ve been treated like I was a broken person for a long time by people. Family, teachers, councilors, whatever it is. I have the difficulty that comes with ADHD, trauma, and depression. Which is hard not to have resentment for. But those things are tied to me and I work to understand and live through them. You don’t look at me like that makes me less than. Nor do you ignore it. You accept that it’s part of me but still show you care.

I hate to have seeded distrust. And that’s entirely on me. I feel truly awful about that.

I hope you do believe me when I say; I care about you a great deal. Not despite anything. Not compared to anyone. Not because you fill any desperate void. Not on any one thing alone. Not even on any expectations for you to be anything in particular at all. I care because you’re you.

The preservation and defensive part of my brain feels like being alone and closed off is safer. You don’t risk getting hurt that way. But you risk a lot more I think if you don’t open yourself up, even in the fear of the potential that getting hurt could happen. You risk missing out on all the potential wonderful moments that could come out of letting someone in.

There can be a pull to live in a protective shell in some way. I may stumble my way through opening up sometimes, but it feels good to be so much myself with you in any context. And I trust you’ll be delicate with an exposed heart.

Whatever it’s been. I’m really liking it.

Through moving day and housework to downtown walks and fire alarm showers.

Between driving at sundown with music as you have your fingers in my hair.

To spying on neighbors and sharing music.

Or waking up, suddenly so excited because I realized where I woke up and who was there.

And every moment in between. It’s all been wonderful.

If we’re still just in the brainstorm of two strangers screenplay. I’m liking the story and am excited to see where it’s going.

As it should be, as in life to get to the other side. For me it goes sideways when those thoughts blend, then you can’t tell what’s irrational bc it all feels real and likely. 

There are many heartbreaking outcomes I could create, but noneee would be the reality. Intention is everything. I could have already decided you would eventually hurt me too bad to mend or run away or change your mind or continue lying. Instead, I chose what I saw far beyond it. You. I do believe you and all that you want me to know you genuinely mean matters so so much to me.

It’s bizarre we let ourselves think into losing someone who is right there, bc a lot of people do just give up or destroy connection to get away easier. That’s why alone seems safer, even though it blocks discovering someone in a kismet way as you’re meant to. Someone that proves you waaay wrong, wants to stick through and grow in and from knowing each other, brings you out of you. Both more alive and themselves as a result 

It’s true for me that in any type of relationship with humans I ultimately offered more than they were willing to or I was used. I hate that it’s true but it is, no matter how careful I was about who I let in even friends. That’s why so many see me as their close friend when to me were just acquaintances. I know I make people feel seen individually, I don’t usually get that back equally. Most find they don’t want someone around that sees what they’re avoiding. 

Even the closest person I had through many years and phases ended up degrading me to get away to avoid accountability. The way people discard and destroy in this one life we have to mend what we can…I can’t grasp. One of the last things he told me was I had so much heart and love to give that no one will ever be able to give that back to me, friend or otherwise. Stacked with a ton of other examples, I slowly silently shut down in a way that really scared me. Like it permanently dulled my light—I’ll take the fear of finding from you that it didn’t anyyy day

The amount of times I suspiciously furrowed my brows in the very first hours of knowing you bc it seemed I was talking to myself or a hallucination of someone I wish I knew was jarring. Perhaps that is what lead to the silence of “…oh god we can’t leave like this what do we do now what is happening everything is happening alreadiii?!” 

I will never not add this because I’ve been made to feel the same—you are actually the opposite of broken. Truly broken people try to break people like us. That’s also how I know we won’t do that to each other. I don’t want to limit us us-ing. I don’t want to fear an end that doesn’t even have to be, if you don’t want that either. And no, you will not find any secret weird addiction. I only have a slight cookie problem sometimes but I think that’s something we can work through. Not even a problem. I don’t have a problem, just love cookies and appreciate the art. But in seriousness, I recognize as a person with depression trauma and adhd that my mind is naturally susceptible to addictive behavior. But I’ve seen it first hand in my parents and I’ve done a lot of reading about it and it’s just really interesting I dunno. I think the antidote to that is transparency and understanding about it and. I have no addictive draw towards drugs or alcohol or sex or anything. I’ve only ever felt like a compulsive relationship to eating really. And that’s never been out of hand really. I appreciate you tellin me that thought. I recognize you aren’t projecting at all and know I’m a different person. But it can be hard not to think about sometimes when you’ve unfortunately been in situations where that happens with people. And I’m sorry that’s happened. That’s incredibly uncomfortable.

I want us both to feel like we can be our entire unadulterated selves. Even if there are things that worry us or we might feel any conflicting way about. I appreciate our ability and willingness to talk through and about things instead of ever letting it build up and become something it doesn’t need to be. That’s how things last, and I think we’re doing a good job. I love us.

In this whirlwind of stress and profound weight I feel. I feel like I am falling apart. I am trying to juggle everything in my life, and I don’t know how. I have been going back and forth between extreme panic, continued hair loss, diarrhea, an unshakable feeling of paranoia like someone is about to jump out at me, night terrors, nausea, tremors in my hands, and rapid heart rate. I feel like I am going crazy. All in between nonstop meetings and jobs where I have to compose myself and having to rush work and stay up for hours on end trying to pull my life and career together so I don’t have a full-on break or run out of money or whatever. I don’t know. Even now I worry I am coming across wrong and doing something wrong, I am just afraid and trying to juggle my life and it’s so overwhelming.

Regardless of this, I know these things are true:

I love you so very much and I want to succeed. I see how much you care and it means so much to me. I have never had that. I care so very much that I don’t know what to do with those feelings sometimes, and I feel so sad, feeling like I am being a disappointment or that I am not enough. I feel like I am not enough; that is not your fault. I know I have a deeply flawed attachment style that I am actively trying to work against and understand. I know I care so deeply, but I also can see that I appear to be so withdrawn and avoidant, entirely without intending to be.

I want you to have the best. I want to be the best I can be for you. I hate that you have any anxiety or fear in any way, much less about me or losing me or anything. I don’t want you to carry anxiety about something, wondering if you’re missing something. 

I care immensely. I love you purely and sincerely. I want you so deeply and madly. I want you to feel, believe, and live that as naturally as breathing.

It also parallels your eye for the details in life and being able to appreciate and take note of them. Far too often, people live at such a rate where they are unable or unwilling to do so. That is so special. You see me and are so generous with yourself, your time, and everything you do.

As I have been trying to calm my mind and figure myself out I’ve further realized how foreign this is to me. To an extent where I feel so threatened and tend to engage in behavior that forces me to withdraw and deactivate. In a way that is not conscious or done with any intent to hurt. I feel so afraid of losing autonomy and independence and being known. I am starting to realize how much closeness and intimacy often scare me until I freeze up and my mind implodes on itself in an effort to try to preserve that independence that isn’t necessarily being threatened in the first place. Coupled with that fear of intimacy and lack of autonomy is also the anxiety that once I am known, I won’t be liked or accepted. 

I don’t want to create a situation in which I am stuck in a vicious cycle of withdrawing out of fear of being known, of intimacy, of feeling like I am not enough, or of being rejected, or of whatever it may be. I don’t want to compound stress so much that it puts a wedge between us further.

I know I need to improve my understanding and ways of expressing where I am and what my needs are. It doesn’t come naturally to me, but I want to improve. Sometimes, I feel uncomfortable when there’s so much attention on me, and it makes me close up or retreat into a shell. I also am very bad at presenting my thoughts unprompted.

I also fear that I will say something incorrectly or be misunderstood. I get so tripped up on my words that it’s hard to express myself, and it takes time to think clearly again.

All of that is exasperated by being genuinely so busy that it is hard to organize everything, stressed about life, and not really in a good place mentally, but earnestly working to improve.

I feel flawed in so many ways. I honestly have trouble viewing myself in a positive light much of the time and believing I am worth a certain level of attention or care. Sometimes, to an extent, that saddens me further or even worries me. I don’t expect you to fix that or prove anything to me. But want to let the assist and care in. I am working on finding that peace in myself. It is taking time, but I am working hard on it.

I guess I just hope that helps in some way, regardless of how imperfect or non-conclusive, fully representative, or comprehensive it may be.

I just don’t want you to have anything less than what you absolutely deserve and feel the care you deserve. I think you’re so wonderful and special. I love you so very much, and I am in awe of you and all that you are.

I can see how my actions might come across as avoidance, and I’m sorry if that’s been hurtful or left you feeling unsure of where we stand. I also see how much this has been weighing on you, and I want to help ease that if I can. 

When you say you shouldn’t have to ask or wait for my availability, I get where you’re coming from. I also want to say that my availability isn’t just about scheduling—it’s about making sure I’m in the right headspace to give you the care and attention you deserve and not add to the stress. I know I have a seemingly more rigid or corporate-sounding vocabulary, I guess. I don’t mean scheduling as in scheduling you into my life like it’s work. I mean scheduling and working on my routine in life so I can feel okay. Not about you being present or anything. I don’t want to show up half-present or distracted though. I know that’s frustrating, and I’m working on finding better ways to balance things and feel okay being present at any moment. But I know this is important, and its not fair not to give it the attention that it deserves.

If something feels urgent or overwhelming for you, I absolutely want you to tell me. I don’t ever want you to feel like you have to hint at things or hold back.

I always want you to feel you’re able to talk to me. Please do. If you need anything I want you to share that. I never said you could not talk to me in any way at all. I don’t always know where to start or anything, but if you have something to say, you don’t need to wait for my permission cue or lead or anything like that. I never intended for it to feel that way if it ever did.

I want you to feel and be able to express things without overthinking them. Even when I know that’s not your intention. It helps me when things are shared as direct requests or needs, like, ‘It would help me if….’ That makes it easier for me to focus and respond without getting lost in my own anxieties.
